---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Convex Optimization & Algorithms | Harutyun Harry Ilanyan">
  <div class="prose max-w-none">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">CVXPY Custom Optimization Toolkit</h1>
    
    <div class="alert alert-warning mb-8">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="stroke-current shrink-0 w-6 h-6">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-2.5L13.732 4c-.77-.833-1.964-.833-2.732 0L3.732 16.5c-.77.833.192 2.5 1.732 2.5z"></path>
      </svg>
      <span>This project is in active development with ongoing algorithm implementations.</span>
    </div>

    <h2>Project Overview</h2>
    <p>
      Advanced optimization algorithms and custom solvers for machine learning applications, featuring Newton and quasi-Newton 
      method implementations with comprehensive performance analysis. This toolkit advances theoretical foundations and practical 
      implementations of optimization methods.
    </p>

    <h2>Key Features</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Custom solver implementations using CVXPY framework</li>
      <li>Newton and quasi-Newton method optimization</li>
      <li>Performance benchmarking and analysis tools</li>
      <li>Algorithm design specifically for ML applications</li>
      <li>Theoretical foundation documentation</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Technical Stack</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6 not-prose">
      <div class="badge badge-primary">Python</div>
      <div class="badge badge-secondary">CVXPY</div>
      <div class="badge badge-accent">Optimization</div>
      <div class="badge badge-info">NumPy</div>
      <div class="badge badge-success">SciPy</div>
      <div class="badge badge-warning">Algorithm Design</div>
    </div>

    <h2>Research Applications</h2>
    <p>
      The toolkit is being applied to various machine learning optimization problems, with focus on enhancing convergence rates 
      and computational efficiency for large-scale applications.
    </p>

    <div class="flex gap-4 mt-8 not-prose">
      <a href="/projects" class="btn btn-outline">‚Üê Back to Projects</a>
      <a href="mailto:harry_ila@berkeley.edu" class="btn btn-primary">Contact for Collaboration</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>